      • registerServiceManager

        <T extends IServiceManager> void registerServiceManager(Class<T> intrface,
                                                      T serviceManager)
        Registers a new IServiceManager instance with the SDK. Once the registration is complete a EventServiceManagerRegistered is posted to the EventBus as returned by getEventBus() this event can be used to implement dependency management among various service managers. For an example see the code in com.palomamobile.android.sdk.notification.NotificationManager as it implements its dependency on com.palomamobile.android.sdk.user.IUserManager implementation. After registering this way the service manager is globally available via the getServiceManager(Class) method.
        Type Parameters:
        T -
        Parameters:
        intrface - contract interface implemented by the serviceManager
        serviceManager - instance of the service manager
